title: Health Inequality and Socioeconomic Stress in Erie County, New York
author: Author A. B.
summary: This analysis focuses on the effects of income disparity, employment status, and education access on healthcare usage in Erie County, New York. It investigates hospital readmissions, vaccination coverage, and chronic disease trends linked to socio-economic pressures.

statistical_analysis.findings: In Erie County, New York, limited access to preventive care and higher unemployment correlated with a 26% increase in preventable hospitalizations. Disparities in health outcomes were more pronounced in low-income ZIP codes (p < 0.05).

policy_implication: This study recommends the expansion of localized health outreach and mobile clinics in Erie County, New York, alongside education grants to support long-term improvements in social determinants of health.
references: Erie County, New York Community Health Needs Assessment
CDC County Health Rankings
U.S. Health and Human Services Reports

statistical_analysis.findings: In Butler County, Ohio, limited access to preventive care and higher unemployment correlated with a 26% increase in preventable hospitalizations. Disparities in health outcomes were more pronounced in low-income ZIP codes (p < 0.05).

policy_implication: This study recommends the expansion of localized health outreach and mobile clinics in Butler County, Ohio, alongside education grants to support long-term improvements in social determinants of health.
references: Butler County, Ohio Community Health Needs Assessment
CDC County Health Rankings
U.S. Health and Human Services Reports
